cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.LG, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with clustering and optimization problems on trees, which are common topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of polytopes and facets suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and linear programming (cs.LG). The problem of decomposing a tree with respect to costs can also be seen as a graph theory problem, which falls under the category of graph theory (cs.GT).
